main event: A 14-year-old observed a luminous object in Beltsville, Maryland on January 24, 1956, which was later suggested to be a time exposure of the moon.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for thirty-three minutes., The object was described as having a long vertical line or rod appearance., The evaluation of the sighting suggested it was a misinterpretation of celestial phenomena., Clear weather conditions were reported at the time., The event was registered under Project Blue Book, which investigated UFO sightings.
witness description: A 14-year-old civilian, student from Beltsville, Maryland.
